						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Brahmapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Tribhuvanavīradēva year 38: 1215-16 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is in characters of about the 13th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of three <hi rend="italic">paḻaṅ-kāśu</hi> by Puttuḻāṉ Periyāṉ Śambuvarāyap-pallavaraiyaṉ for maintaining a perpetual lamp to the deity Tiruvayanīśuram-uḍaiyār of Vaḻugūr. The <hi rend="italic">Śivabrāhmaṇas</hi> undertook to maintain the endowment from out of three <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> received from the donor.</p>						

						</summary>
